item.title: I dont know how to portforward help me
item.dc:creator: @aquatizscape aquatizscape
item.description:
@aquatizscape wrote:

It depends what kind of router you have.
Usually, just go to Start>run>Cmd.
Type in ipconfig then push enter.
Look for the one that says default gateway, and type that number into your browser. then, you click virtual servers, or whatever it says on your router, and make a new thing called RSPS. make the ports 43594, and the little ip thing should include the last number of your gateway. Save it, and i hope i helped!
